Maiduguri – The Police in Maiduguri have confirmed Boko Haram attack on Jakana town in Konduga Local Government Area of Borno State. A statement by Police Public Relations Officer of Borno State Command, Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) Edet Okon stated that, the insurgents who came to the town in about 30 vehicles launched their attacks at about 6 pm on Thursday. The statement further explained that, security forces, including police combat units were deployed for reinforcement, and had successfully repelled the insurgents. Meanwhile, it was not disclosed whether there were casualties or not during the attack. But it was gathered that, residents of Jakana fled the town for safety. Our correspondent discovers that, Jakana town is not too far away from Benisheik which is on the Maiduguri Kano Road and it  is about 50 kilometres from the Borno State capital. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 